  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Process Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Drive operational excellence by leading process optimization initiatives, analyzing data to improve efficiency, and managing projects that enhance petrochemical or refining processes. Collaborate cross-functionally to ensure compliance and deliver measurable improvements.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Identify and implement process improvements to increase efficiency, reduce costs, and maintain compliance with safety and environmental standards</li><li>Analyze process data to detect trends, troubleshoot operational issues, and develop continuous improvement strategies</li><li>Lead or contribute to project initiatives focused on upgrading or expanding existing processes, ensuring projects meet timelines and budget targets</li><li>Collaborate with operations, maintenance, and safety teams to resolve process-related challenges and achieve operational excellence</li><li>Ensure all processes comply with local and international safety, environmental, and quality regulations and standards</li><li>Maintain accurate and current documentation of processes, procedures, and engineering calculations to support operational integrity</li><li>Provide training and guidance to operators to improve process understanding and promote adherence to best practices</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Chemical Engineering or a related field</li><li>3-5 years of practical experience in process engineering within the petrochemical or refining industry</li><li>Proficiency in process simulation tools such as Aspen Plus and Excel-based calculations</li><li>Familiarity with safety and environmental regulations specific to the petrochemical sector</li><li>Demonstrated problem-solving and analytical skills applied to process engineering challenges</li><li>Effective communication skills to facilitate teamwork and cross-functional collaboration</li><li>Project management experience</li><li>SCEM and/or Water Efficiency Manager certification</li></ul>",
